Privacy Policy of Urban Rivals (Acute Games SAS)
At Acute Games SAS, we take the protection of your personal data very seriously. This privacy policy describes the types of personal data we collect, how we use it, and the measures we take to protect your data.
Types of data collected: We collect information such as your username, email address, IP address, and payment information (if applicable). These information are used to allow you to play Urban Rivals, to send you notification emails, and to process transactions.
Use of data: We use your data to allow you to play Urban Rivals, to send you notification emails, and to process transactions. We may also use your data to improve our service.
Data protection: We take security measures to protect your data from loss, misuse, and unauthorized access. We use standard security technologies to protect data stored on our servers.
Data deletion: If you wish to delete your data, please contact our customer support at moderator@urban-rivals.com. We will respond within 48 business hours.
Changes to Privacy Policy: We reserve the right to modify this privacy policy at any time. Any changes will be posted on this page.
Contact Us: If you have any questions about our privacy policy, please contact us at moderator@urban-rivals.com
Cookies: We use cookies to track your use of the site and to personalize your gaming experience. Cookies are small files that are stored on your computer or mobile device when you visit our site. They allow us to identify you when you return to our site and to remember your preferences. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but this may affect your ability to use certain features of our site.
Data sharing: We will not share your personal data with third parties, except as necessary to provide a service or to comply with applicable laws and regulations. We may share anonymous information with commercial partners for research and analysis purposes.
User rights: In accordance with applicable regulations, you have the right to access, rectify, and delete your personal data. You may also object to the processing of your personal data and set post-mortem directives. To exercise these rights, please contact our customer support at moderator@urban-rivals.com.
Liability: We make every effort to protect your personal data, but we cannot guarantee absolute security. By using our service, you acknowledge that you understand and accept this risk.
International data transfer: If you use our service from a country other than where our servers are located, your data may be transferred outside of your home country. By using our service, you consent to this data transfer.
Children: Our service is intended for individuals aged 12 and older. We do not intentionally collect personal data from children under the age of 12. If we discover that we have collected personal data from a child under the age of 12, we will take necessary measures to delete that data and verify that the individuals providing that data are the child's legal parents or guardians. We encourage parents or guardians to monitor Internet use by children under the age of 12.
Links to other sites: Our site may contain links to other sites that are not operated by us. We are not responsible for the privacy policies or practices of these sites. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of any site you visit.
Conflict Resolution: If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please contact us at moderator@urban-rivals.com. We will make every effort to resolve any conflicts in a timely and efficient manner.
Compliance with regulations: We comply with all applicable laws and regulations regarding privacy and data protection, including the European Union's General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
Name and address of data protection officer: If you have any questions about how we handle your personal data, you can contact our data protection officer at the following address: dpo@acute-games.com
This privacy policy is effective from the date of publication and will remain in effect except for changes made by Acute Games SAS. We reserve the right to update this privacy policy at any time by publishing the new version on our website.
We use cookies on this site to enhance your user experience. By continuing to browse our website, you are giving your consent for us to set cookies.